 mechanisms if you need to move between   multiple MPI implementations because support for it is not likely to be   portable.</font></span></div>  <div><span class="041595110-26052006"><font color="#0000ff" face="Arial" size="2"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>  <div><span class="041595110-26052006"><font color="#0000ff" face="Arial" size="2">Within   Open MPI, fork() will almost certainly fail&nbsp;if you use&nbsp;the OS-bypass   networks (Myrinet, InfiniBand).&nbsp; The mechanisms that these networks use for   high-speed/low latency are quite problematic with fork().&nbsp; If you are using   tcp or shared memory, fork() *might* work, but this is not something that we   have extensively tested.</font></span></div><br>  <blockquote style="border-left: 2px solid rgb(0, 0, 255); padding-left: 5px; margin-left: 5px; margin-right: 0px;" dir="ltr">    <div class="OutlookMessageHeader" align="left" dir="ltr" lang="en-us">    <hr tabindex="-1">    <font face="Tahoma"
